## Code Generation

```rust
fn generate_helper_structs(
    name: &Ident,
    parsed: &ParsedSignature,
    vis: &Visibility,
) -> proc_macro2::TokenStream {
    let input_name = format_ident!("{}Input", name);
    let output_name = format_ident!("__{}Output", name);
    let all_name = format_ident!("__{}All", name);

    // Input struct fields
    let input_fields: Vec<_> = parsed.input_fields.iter().map(|f| {
        let ident = &f.ident;
        let ty = &f.ty;
        quote! { pub #ident: #ty }
    }).collect();

    // Output struct fields
    let output_fields: Vec<_> = parsed.output_fields.iter().map(|f| {
        let ident = &f.ident;
        let ty = &f.ty;
        quote! { pub #ident: #ty }
    }).collect();

    // All struct fields (input + output)
    let all_fields: Vec<_> = parsed.input_fields.iter()
        .chain(parsed.output_fields.iter())
        .map(|f| {
            let ident = &f.ident;
            let ty = &f.ty;
            quote! { pub #ident: #ty }
        }).collect();

    quote! {
        #[derive(Debug, Clone, ::dspy_rs::BamlType)]
        #vis struct #input_name {
            #(#input_fields),*
        }

        #[doc(hidden)]
        #[derive(Debug, Clone, ::dspy_rs::BamlType)]
        pub struct #output_name {
            #(#output_fields),*
        }

        #[doc(hidden)]
        #[derive(Debug, Clone, ::dspy_rs::BamlType)]
        pub struct #all_name {
            #(#all_fields),*
        }
    }
}
```

## Preserving Doc Comments

Doc comments should transfer to generated structs for documentation:

```rust
let input_fields: Vec<_> = parsed.input_fields.iter().map(|f| {
    let ident = &f.ident;
    let ty = &f.ty;
    let doc = &f.description;
    if doc.is_empty() {
        quote! { pub #ident: #ty }
    } else {
        quote! {
            #[doc = #doc]
            pub #ident: #ty
        }
    }
}).collect();
```

## Visibility

- QAInput: Same visibility as original struct (usually `pub`)
- __QAOutput, __QAAll: Hidden but `pub` for macro hygiene

